The paper addresses the problem of coordination of a fleet of mobile robots, which is a core topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach is based on a probabilistic algorithm (RRT) and involves optimization and decision-making processes, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also presents experimental results, which may fall under the category of machine learning (cs.MA) or data analysis (cs.LG).
